    <p>To exercise the right specified in this section, please submit a written request to our Company.</p>
    <p><strong>Application processing procedure</strong></p>
    <p>In order to protect the data of all our candidates and buyers from unauthorized disclosure, we, upon receiving your request to provide data or exercise your other rights, will be required to identify you. For this purpose, we may ask you to provide the relevant profile data you have provided (e.g. name, e-mail address or phone number) and we will compare whether the data you have provided matches the relevant profile data. As part of this check, we may also send a control message to the contact specified in the registration form (by SMS or e-mail) asking for an authorization step. If the verification procedure is unsuccessful (for example, the data you provided in the form do not match the data specified in the form or you do not authorize according to the received SMS or e-mail message), we will be forced to state that you are not the subject of the requested data and we will be obliged reject your request.</p>
    <p>Upon receiving your request for the implementation of any of your rights and successfully completing the verification procedure specified above, we undertake to provide you with information about the actions without undue delay, but in any case no later than one month after receiving your request and completing the verification procedure, which we took according to your request. Taking into account the complexity and number of requests, we have the right to extend the one-month period for another two months, informing you of this before the end of the first month and indicating the reasons for such an extension.</p>
